<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-38-0095 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this paper some of the broader aspects of emission control are discussedand it is shown that there are various ways of achieving emission reductions.In the field of sulphur dioxide emission control the merits and optimizationof coal cleaning, coal re-routing, flue gas desulphurization and advancedcombustion technologies are discussed. It is shown that in all theseareas a close integration and optimization of the total process fromreagent supply to product disposal is required. Some of the problemsof integrating these technologies into the existing chemical infrastructureare also discussed.</TEXT></DOC>